    },
    {
      "id": "805ab5fd_aeab4b64",
      "file_path": "scripts/policy/docker-compose-all.yml",
      "patchset_number": 7,
      "line": 33,
      "message": "I agree, it would be better to use a different hostname if it was possible for the simulators, I find it too a bit obscure when configuring components to point to the simulators server with this name.   I suspect that this is used with this name to reuse one of the available names in the certificate for https.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 477,
        "name": "Jorge Hernandez",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jorge.hernandez-herrero@att.com",
        "username": "jhh"
      },
      "updated": "2020-09-22 15:01:05.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "d82f43cf_09c6e95f",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "f1c48024_8f79c2ca",
      "file_path": "scripts/policy/docker-compose-all.yml",
      "patchset_number": 7,
      "line": 33,
      "message": "It is exactly as Jorge says - because HTTPS is used, the certificate used by the simulator must appear in the certificate file; originally chose this for expediency and have never taken the time to change it.  If Jorge can provide an updated cert file with an additional certificate, we can change it, though I don't know if we can change it to \"message-router\" since that's already in use (but maybe?) - thus no way to avoid the need to overlay the defaultConfig.json in all of the other components.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 811,
        "name": "Jim Hahn",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jrh3@att.com",
        "username": "jrh3"
      },
      "updated": "2020-09-28 14:06:07.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "805ab5fd_aeab4b64",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "d78515b4_6ab06fed",
      "file_path": "scripts/policy/docker-compose-all.yml",
      "patchset_number": 7,
      "line": 168,
      "message": "at least for the CSITs, things run a lot smoother/faster if the things on which they depend are already running.  For example, if a PDP sends its registration message before PAP is running, then it will have to wait a whole other cycle before it's actually registered. These lines ensure the prerequisites are ready first.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 811,
        "name": "Jim Hahn",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jrh3@att.com",
        "username": "jrh3"
      },
      "updated": "2020-09-28 14:06:07.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "c0c7a707_66c78338",
      "unresolved": true
    },
